8. The reason for centering age around group mean was that the raw scores of age could lead to nonsensical results in the above equation (Raudenbush & Bryk, 2002, p. 32). The intercept, hoj, would be the expected outcome for an inmate in prison j who had a zero of age. Thus, the hoj parameter was meaningless in this instance because the age of an inmate was never a value of zero. Also, centering stabilized the model (Kreft & de Leeuw, 1998, p. 114). This technical advantage was confirmed in this study in the process of the data analysis. For example, before centering, adding, or deleting variable(s) in the model led to big changes in the estimate of g00 and the estimated value of g00 was distorted.
